      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that the person you loved is gone and that you are left with nothing but an empty shell. When a part of yourself seems dead, the natural reaction is to feel hopeless about the future and wonder why anyone would want to keep going. However, this feeling of emptiness is often a symptom of deep grief rather than a permanent reality, and it does not mean you should stop trying to find meaning. Please consider reaching out to a crisis counselor or therapist who can help you process this profound loss and support you through this difficult time.",
